1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Qe7 5. Bg2 Nc6 6. e3 e5 7. d5 Nb8 8. Nc3 {
Now this is best - White wants to secure the pair of bishops.} (8. Ne2 $5) 8...
a6 (8... a5 9. Nge2 d6 10. a3 Bxc3 (10... Bc5 11. Na4) 11. Nxc3 O-O {How
should White play?} 12. e4 $1 {Black had the positional threat to play ...e4,
when White risks ending up with a passive dark-squared bishop. After 12.e4!
White has an advantage in space and the pair of bishops to boot.}) 9. Nge2 Bc5
10. Qc2 $16 {Black preserved his bishop but he has lost a lot of time. White
is better due to his advantage in space.} d6 11. b4 (11. h3 $5 {with the idea
of g4, Ng3 was interesting. In the game, White won after a complicated fight.})
11... Ba7 12. O-O O-O 13. h3 h5 14. e4 Nh7 15. Kh2 h4 16. Qd3 Nd7 17. Rae1 Re8
18. f4 hxg3+ 19. Nxg3 exf4 20. Nf5 Qg5 21. Bxf4 Ne5 22. Qd1 Qg6 23. c5 dxc5 24.
Re3 cxb4 25. Rg3 Bxf5 26. exf5 Qxg3+ 27. Bxg3 bxc3 28. Qb3 Bc5 29. Qxc3 Bd6 30.
Re1 Nf6 31. Rxe5 Bxe5 32. Bxe5 Nh5 33. Bf3 Nf6 34. Bxf6 gxf6 35. Qxf6 Rad8 36.
