1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Qe7 5. Bg2 Bxd2+ 6. Qxd2 d6 7. e3 e5 8.
Ne2 O-O 9. Nbc3 exd4 10. exd4 $16 (10. Nxd4 $5 $16) 10... c6 11. O-O Bf5 12. h3
$1 {I prepare g4, Ng3. Vacating the e-file with Nf4 is inferior, since then
the knight would not have any perspective on f4.} Na6 13. Rfe1 Qd7 14. g4 $1
Bg6 15. f4 $1 $18 {Black can save his bishop but it will nevertheless remain
totally out of play. I encourage you to study the rest of this instructive
textbook game!} h6 16. f5 Bh7 17. Ng3 Rfe8 18. Bf3 Rxe1+ 19. Rxe1 Re8 20. h4
