1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 $1 d5 {This is a solid and
playable system for Black. I suggest it in my repertoire on the Bogo-Indian as
a 2nd choice.} 6. Bg2 (6. Nc3 $6 {would be a mistake since after} dxc4 {
it's not easy to regain the pawn.}) 6... c6 (6... dxc4 $6 7. Na3 $14) (6... O-O
7. Nf3 {may transpose to the game.} (7. Nc3 $2 dxc4 8. Nf3 Nc6 $15)) 7. Nf3
Nbd7 (7... dxc4 $2 8. Ne5 $16) 8. Qc2 O-O 9. Nbd2 b6 10. O-O {White enjoys a
nice position, though Black is quite solid.} Bb7 11. Rad1 Qb8 $6 12. Rfe1 h6 {
Black plays too passively and drifts into a worse position.} 13. e4 dxe4 14.
Nxe4 Nxe4 15. Qxe4 c5 16. Qe3 cxd4 17. Rxd4 $14 Nf6 18. Qe5 $2 {This serious
mistake throws away the advantage, though in the game, Black did not grab his
chance.} (18. Red1 $16) 18... Qxe5 (18... Bxf3 $1 19. Bxf3 Qxe5 20. Rxe5 Rad8
$15) 19. Nxe5 Bxg2 20. Kxg2 $14 {Now, White is better again.} Rfd8 21. Red1
Rxd4 22. Rxd4 Rc8 23. h4 (23. b4 {Let me demonstrate a typical idea:} Kf8 24.
b5 Rc7 25. Nc6 $16) 23... Kf8 24. g4 Rc7 25. b4 Ke8 26. b5 Nd7 27. Nc6 a5 28.
Rd6 g5 29. hxg5 hxg5 30. Kf3 Kf8 31. Ke3 Kg7 32. Kd4 Kf8 33. f3 Ke8 34. Kc3 Kf8
35. Rd1 Kg7 36. Rd6 Kf8 37. Kd2 Kg7 38. Ke3 Kf8 39. f4 gxf4+ 40. Kxf4 Kg7 41.
g5 Kh7 42. g6+ Kg7 43. gxf7 Kxf7 44. Kg5 Nc5 45. Ne5+ Ke7 46. Rxb6 Nd7 47. Nc6+
Kd6 48. Ra6 Kc5 49. Nxa5 Kb4 50. Kf4 e5+ 51. Ke3 Nc5 52. Ra8 Rh7 53. b6 Rh3+
54. Ke2 Rh2+ 55. Kf3 Rxa2 56. Nc6+ Kb3 57. Rxa2 Kxa2 58. Nxe5 Kb3 59. Ke3 Kc3
60. Nd3 Nd7 61. b7 Nb8 62. Ne5 Kb4 63. Kd4 Ka5 64. Kc5 Na6+ 65. Kc6 Nb8+ 66.
Kc7 Na6+ 67. Kc8 1-0

