1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 d5 6. Bg2 O-O 7. Nf3 c6 8.
b3 {An unusual idea, that seems playable.} (8. O-O {is the usual move.}) 8...
b6 (8... Ne4 {does not lead to anything for Black.} 9. Qc2 Qa5+ 10. Nbd2 Nxd2
11. Nxd2 $16 ({Even} 11. Qxd2 Qxd2+ 12. Nxd2 {leads to an advantage for White.}
(12. Kxd2 $5))) 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Rc1 Ba6 11. a4 $1 $14 {This is very common
motif in the Catalan. When White chooses a setup with rooks on c1 and a1, he
can target a Black bishop on a6 with a4-a5.} Qe7 12. a5 Rfd8 13. Qf4 c5 14.
Nbd2 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Qe8 16. Nc6 Rdc8 17. Qd6 Bb7 18. Ne7+ 1-0

