e5 9. O-O {In general, White will continue with a3.} Qc7 (9... Nc6 10. a3 bxa3
11. Rxa3 Nb4 12. Nbc3 $14 {White has a nice, risk-free advantage.}) 10. Qb3 (
10. Nd2 $5 a5 11. a3 $14) (10. b3 $5 a5 11. a3 $14) 10... a5 11. a3 Na6 12.
axb4 axb4 (12... Nxb4 13. Na3 $5 $14) 13. Nd2 Be6 14. Qd3 $14 ({We do not want
to play} 14. d5 $2 {since this would give up control of the c5-square, which
the a6-knight can use.} Bg4 15. f3 Bd7 16. e4 Qb6+ 17. Kh1 Nc5 $15) 14... Rfe8
15. b3 Rad8 16. h3 Qc8 17. g4 h5 18. f3 e4 19. Nxe4 Nxe4 20. fxe4 hxg4 21. hxg4
