1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 c5 5. Bxb4 cxb4 6. Bg2 O-O 7. e3 a5 8. Ne2
d6 9. O-O Na6 10. a3 $1 {The typical method in this line.} e5 11. axb4 axb4 {
Black wants to prevent Nc3, but now the pawn on b4 is a permanent weakness.} (
11... Nxb4 12. Nbc3 $14) 12. Nd2 $14 Qe7 13. h3 {White prevents Bg4, which
would have been annoying, and prepares a possible g4, Ng3.} (13. Re1 Bg4 $132)
13... Re8 14. Qc2 Qc7 (14... exd4 15. Nxd4 $16 {gives Black access to c5, but
White's knight on d4 is quite powerful.}) 15. g4 $5 h6 16. Ng3 $16 Be6 17. Rac1
Rac8 18. Qd3 Bd7 19. f4 exd4 20. exd4 Nh7 21. Nde4 Qb6 22. Qd2 Be6 23. b3 f6
24. Kh2 Re7 25. Rfe1 Rce8 26. c5 dxc5 27. dxc5 Qa5 28. Nd6 Rd8 29. Ngf5 1-0

