Nbd7 $6 (11... Qxd4 12. Nxd4 Bxg2 13. Kxg2 Na6 $14 {/=}) 12. Nc3 Bc5 13. Qh4
O-O 14. Bf4 Rc8 15. Rad1 {White has some pressure - his pieces are much more
active.} Qe8 16. Bh3 Be7 17. Nd4 Nd5 18. Bg5 Bxg5 19. Qxg5 h6 20. Qd2 Nxc3 21.
bxc3 (21. Qxc3 $18 {was best, when White has a decisive positional advantage.
Yet after 21.bxc3, White had an original idea in mind:}) 21... Ba4 22. Rb1 Rb8
23. Rb4 $5 {The rook is suddenly transferred to the kingside.} Nf6 $2 (23...
Ne5 $14) 24. Nf5 $18 Bc6 25. Rh4 Ne4 26. Nxh6+ $1 Kh7 27. Bf5+ 1-0

