1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 a6 8. a4
Bd7 9. Qxc4 Bc6 10. Bf4 a5 11. Nc3 Na6 12. Rfe1 (12. Rac1 {is our repertoire
suggestion.}) 12... Bxf3 $6 {This idea is playable only when White has
exchanged his dark-squared bishop.} 13. Bxf3 c6 14. e4 $16 Nb4 15. Rad1 Nd7 16.
d5 {White is already close to winning. Let's suppose that d4-d5 was not
possible - what are White's alternatives?} (16. h4 $5 {is White's 2nd best
move. In this position, we do not want to play h5, but to prevent ...Bg5.} g5
$2 {would create major weaknesses. For example} 17. hxg5 Bxg5 18. Bd6 (18. Bxg5
Qxg5 19. Kg2 Kh8 20. Rh1 $18) 18... Be7 19. Bxe7 Qxe7 20. Kg2 $18) (16. Bg2 {
If White plays a random move, then} Bg5 {would decrease White's advantage.} 17.
Bxg5 (17. Bd6 $6 Nb6 $11) 17... Qxg5 18. f4 $6 Qe7 $14) 16... e5 17. dxc6 (17.
Be3 $5 Nc2 $140 18. dxc6 $1 Nxe1 19. Bg4 $1 $18) 17... bxc6 18. Bg4 Nb6 19. Qe2
$16 Qc7 20. Be3 Rfd8 21. h4 Rxd1 22. Rxd1 Rd8 23. b3 h6 24. Rxd8+ Qxd8 25. Nd1
Nc8 26. Bxc8 Qxc8 27. Nb2 Kf8 $6 (27... Bd8 28. Nc4 Bc7 29. Bc5 $1 (29. Bd2 $5)
29... Na6 30. Ba3 $18) (27... c5 28. Nc4 Nc6 29. Qd2 $16) 28. Nc4 $18 1-0

