1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. d4 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 a6 8. a4
Bd7 9. Qxc4 Bc6 10. Bf4 Bd6 11. Qc1 Nbd7 12. a5 ({I would have chosen} 12. Nc3
$14) 12... Qe7 13. Nc3 e5 {It seems that Black frees his position with this,
but White still keeps some advantage in the endgame after} 14. dxe5 Nxe5 15.
Nxe5 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Bxe5 17. Qe3 $1 Rfe8 18. Qxe5 Qxe5 19. Bxe5 Rxe5 20. Rfd1
$14 {This endgame is not equal - Black's queenside majority is immobile, White
controls the only open file, and his king is better placed.} h5 21. Ra4 $5 b5
22. axb6 cxb6 23. e4 b5 24. Rad4 a5 25. f4 Re6 26. e5 (26. Kf3 $5) 26... b4 27.
Rd8+ Rxd8 28. Rxd8+ Kh7 29. Nb5 {In order to fight for the win, White has to
keep the knights on the board.} (29. exf6 {would be insufficient due to} bxc3
30. fxg7 Kxg7 31. bxc3 Re3 32. Rd5 Kg6 33. Rxa5 Rxc3 $14 {/= The rook endgame
will most likely end in a draw despite White's extra pawn.}) 29... Ne4 30. Kf3
Rb6 31. Nd4 Nc5 32. Rd5 Nd3 33. b3 $16 a4 34. bxa4 b3 35. Rb5 Rxb5 36. Nxb5 Nc5
$6 37. a5 $18 b2 38. Nc3 Kg6 39. g4 hxg4+ 40. Kxg4 f5+ 41. Kf3 Kh5 42. h3 Kh4
43. Kg2 Ne6 44. a6 1-0

