b4 9. Nbd2 a5 $2 {Black loses time and the pawn remains a target on a5.} 10.
Nxc4 Bb7 11. Bg5 (11. Be3 $5) 11... Be4 12. Qd2 (12. Qb3 $5) 12... h6 13. Bxf6
Bxf6 14. Rfd1 Qe7 15. Rac1 Rd8 16. Qf4 $16 {White has achieved a big advantage
with simple means.} Bxf3 17. Qxf3 Ra7 18. Qe3 Ra6 19. Ne5 Rad6 20. h4 Qe8 21.
b3 Na6 22. Bc6 Qe7 23. Rc4 Bxe5 $6 {Now Black's queenside collapses, but it
was difficult to defend Black's position in any case.} 24. Qxe5 Nb8 25. Bf3 f6
26. Qxa5 $18 e5 27. Qxb4 exd4 28. Rdxd4 Na6 29. Qd2 Qe5 30. e3 Qf5 31. Kg2 Qb1
32. Rxd6 Rxd6 33. Rd4 Qxb3 34. Rxd6 cxd6 35. Bd5+ 1-0

