1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O Nbd7 7. Qc2 c6 8. Nbd2
b6 9. e4 $1 Nxe4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Qxe4 Bb7 12. Rd1 $1 Rc8 (12... b5 $5 13. b3
$1 (13. c5 $4 {would be strategically desirable but runs into} Nxc5 $17) ({
White can win a pawn with} 13. cxb5 {but after} Nf6 14. Qe2 cxb5 15. Qxb5 Rb8 {
Black obtains some counterplay for it.}) 13... bxc4 14. bxc4 $14) (12... Qc7
13. Bf4 Bd6 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. c5 $1 Qc7 16. b4 a5 17. a3 Nf6 18. Qc2 Nd5 19.
Qb2 Rfd8 20. Ne5 $16) 13. Bf4 Nf6 14. Qc2 {14.Qe2 is also possible.} (14. Qe2
Bd6 15. Ne5 Qe7 16. Rd3 c5 (16... Rfd8 17. Rad1 Ba8 18. g4 $16) 17. dxc5 Bxc5
18. Rad1 Bxg2 19. Kxg2 Qb7+ 20. Qf3 Qxf3+ 21. Kxf3 Rfe8 22. g4 h6 23. h4 $16)
14... Bd6 15. Bxd6 Qxd6 16. c5 $1 Qe7 (16... bxc5 17. dxc5 Qc7 18. Rd6 $5 $16 (
18. Nd2 $5 {[%csl Gd6][%cal Yd2c4,Yc4d6]})) 17. b4 Nd5 18. Rab1 b5 {Black's
position was difficult in any case but now it looks hopeless.} 19. h4 h6 20.
Ne5 Rfd8 ({After a random move like} 20... a6 $16 {White can even play} 21.
Bxd5 $16 {, though it isn't necessary.} (21. Rb3 $5 $18) (21. Be4 $5 Rfd8 22.
Bh7+ (22. Rb3 $18) 22... Kh8 23. Bg6 $1 $18)) 21. Rb3 Rc7 22. Be4 Nf6 23. Rf3
Qe8 (23... Nxe4 24. Rxf7) 24. Bd3 Re7 25. Qc1 (25. Rxf6 $3 gxf6 26. Ng4 Kg7 27.
Qd2 $18) 25... Nd7 26. Bc2 {White is slowly preparing to build a queen and
bishop battery.} Nxe5 27. dxe5 Rd5 (27... Rxd1+ 28. Qxd1 Rd7 29. Rd3 Rxd3 30.
Qxd3 g6 31. Qd6 $18) 28. Bb3 Rxd1+ $2 ({Black should have tried} 28... Rxe5 29.
Rfd3 Rd5 {though it's not enough after} 30. Bxd5 exd5 31. Re3 $18) 29. Qxd1 Rd7
30. Rd3 Rxd3 31. Qxd3 $18 {This endgame is hopeless for Black.} h5 32. Bc2 g6
33. Qd6 Bc8 34. Be4 Bd7 35. Qc7 a6 36. Bf3 Kf8 37. Kg2 Kg7 38. Qb7 Qd8 39. Qxa6
Qc7 40. a4 bxa4 41. Qxa4 Kf8 42. Qa5 Qxa5 43. bxa5 Ke7 44. a6 Bc8 45. Be2 ({
I will point out that this endgame is even winning for White without the
a6-pawn:} 45. Be4 Bxa6 46. Bf3 Bb7 47. Be4 Ba8 48. Kf3 Kf8 49. Kf4 Kg7 50. Kg5
Bb7 51. f3 Ba8 52. g4 hxg4 53. fxg4 Bb7 54. h5 gxh5 55. gxh5 Ba8 56. h6+ Kg8
57. Kf6 $18) 45... Kd8 46. Kf3 Ke7 47. Kf4 Kf8 48. a7 Bb7 49. a8=Q+ Bxa8 50.
Kg5 Kg7 51. Ba6 1-0

