1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 Be7 5. d4 O-O 6. Nc3 (6. O-O c6 7. Qc2 {
is our move order, which can also lead to the position in the game (see the
previous game).}) 6... c6 7. Qd3 b6 8. b3 Ba6 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Bb2 Rc8 11. Rfd1
c5 (11... Re8 12. e4 $14 (12. Rac1 $14)) 12. Nb5 $1 Bxb5 13. cxb5 Qc7 14. Rac1
Qb7 15. a4 Ne4 ({Structurally speaking, Black is doing well after} 15... cxd4
16. Nxd4 Nc5 17. Qb1 $16 {, but soon a white knight will appear on c6.}) 16.
Ne5 (16. Rc2 $5 $14 {/+/-}) 16... Nxe5 17. dxe5 f5 18. exf6 Bxf6 (18... Nxf6 $2
19. Bh3 $16) 19. Bxf6 (19. Bxe4 $1 dxe4 20. Qc2 $14) 19... Nxf6 $11 20. e4 dxe4
21. Qe2 Rfd8 22. Rc4 Rxd1+ 23. Qxd1 Qd5 24. Qc2 Rd8 25. Bxe4 Qd1+ 26. Kg2 Rd2
27. Qxd1 Rxd1 28. Kf3 Kf7 29. Bc2 Ra1 30. b4 cxb4 31. Rxb4 Ra3+ 32. Kg2 Rc3 33.
Be4 Ke7 34. Bc6 e5 35. a5 Ra3 36. axb6 axb6 37. Rc4 Rb3 38. Ra4 e4 39. Ra7+ Kf8
40. Rb7 Rb2 41. Kf1 e3 42. fxe3 Ng4 43. Rxb6 Nxe3+ 44. Ke1 Rxh2 45. Rb7 Rc2 46.
Be4 Rb2 47. b6 Nc4 48. Rb8+ Ke7 49. b7 Nd6 50. Bf3 Rb3 51. Kf2 Kf6 52. Rf8+ 1-0

