f5 11. Nbd2 Nhf6 12. Ne1 $5 Ne4 13. Ndf3 Bd6 14. Nd3 Qe7 15. Bf4 $16 (15. b3 g5
$2 16. Nfe5 $1 $16)) 11. Nbd2 $1 {The inclusion of the moves ...Nh5 - Bc1 -
Nhf6 has helped White since now he can develop with Nbd2!} b6 12. e4 Bb7 13. e5
Ne8 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. Re1 Qc8 (15... Rc8 16. Qd1 Qc7 17. Nb1 $5 $16) 16. Qd1 a5
(16... Ba6 17. Nb1 (17. Nf1) 17... Bb4 18. Bd2 Bxd2 19. Qxd2 $16) 17. h4 Ba6
18. Nf1 b5 19. Bg5 $1 $16 {Trading the dark-squared bishops is a typical idea
in these positions!} Bxg5 20. hxg5 b4 21. Ne3 Qb7 22. Ng4 Rc8 23. Qd2 Kh8 24.
Bf1 $1 Bxf1 25. Rxf1 Nc7 26. Kg2 Rg8 27. Rh1 Nf8 28. g6 $1 fxg6 29. Ng5 h5 30.
